reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars S24 ultra screen protector
reviews.reviewText: Product turned out great. Very clear and easy to install

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Fingerprint Security may or may not work
reviews.reviewText: First the Fingerprint Security didn't work at all. Tried it a few days later and it worked. Was able the delete the old settings and create a new one. It took a while to do it, but eventually it worked.Well, I was happy. The screen was very easy to put on. The easiest one I ever tried.Well, back to the Fingerprint settings...it works sometimes now.Be that as it may, I still really like it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars I should have listened to the other comments
reviews.reviewText: These are meant to be tempered glass protectors but they're so flaccid I broke one wiggling it around but not until it was bent nearly 90 degrees.It does not fit edge to edge and as soon as it was on there were already specks of things getting through to the edges. Twice my fingernail has snagged the edge and it immediately was lifting because the adhesion is very poor.I will say thugg my fingerprint sensor is a little more picky but it still works fine and the screen protector will probably last at least a few weeks

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Samsung S23 Ultra beware
reviews.reviewText: The screen was easy to put on, that's where the good news ends. There's a circle where your finger sensor is located that's always visible on the screen. In addition, it's very hard to get the sensor to work with this screen protector. I always use biometrics to unlock my phone and for passwords so this is very frustrating. My original screen cover (flexible kind) didn't have this issue. I don't recommend this protector, it's best to keep looking. That's what I'm doing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Do not buy this product. Fingerprint sensor doesn't work once you put the cover on your phone. Barely an instructions included, all or which are misspelled or don't make sense. There is a huge circular fingerprint mark on the screen protector now, even though it doesn't work. Very disappointed. Can't even return because I had to use both covers after the first one shattered.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Spiderwebbed instantly and didn't stay on
reviews.reviewText: The first thing I noticed when I got this was the crappy camera protector sticker things, they're pretty awkward but I figured hey that's ok, at least I got a quality screen protector, right? Wrong. After having it for 4 days my phone fell two feet onto a carpeted floor and this screen protector popped off like paper and spiderwebbed like hell. I will be choosing a different brand next time but this gets 2 stars for at least protecting my screen, even if it is only once.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Fingerprint Reader Doesn't Work. Neither Does the Rest
reviews.reviewText: I did all the things with the fingerprint reader, but since they put adhesive under it, it doesn't work. When I went to settings to check my added fingerprints, 50% of the time it didn't recognize it at all, 25% of the time it did, and 25% of the time it said it was a different fingerprint. Why do they insist on messing with that single area??This morning, I dropped my phone approximately 3.5' to the ground and the thing just popped off entirely.The instructions are comically badly translated. I thought I was having a stroke or something!TLDR: find something better.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars camera protection was not included
reviews.reviewText: How ridiculous to include a cameral protector that is not even the right size nor form. The screen protector did work fine however. So I am keeping that. Now I need to order the lens protector separately. Is that even an option? What a pain.
